159F46C3.Line37.7FA05: Brother, no. Get to the Tree, now! Stop him!

2810B8F0.Line7.7FA05: Leaving? We go to face Lilith. I had hoped you would join us.

47AEBA84.Line31.6DE47: Lorath could ask, but he'll have to pay the price.

5A196F77.Line1.789BF: Ahh, I hear laughter on the wind. Elias' head hangs from the Tree of Whispers. And your soulstone is attuned. This is where I leave you.

65D57290.VoiceDir37.7FA05: Deep grief and alarm. Barking orders, desperate.

6E8CB2DA.Line17.BAE4: I've not seen him since...since Elias spent his last words calling him a coward.

7B97AD88.Line35.6DE47: The same Elias paid. Eternity on the Tree.

8E02627B.Line5.789BF: I know the weight of your reasons, but Lilith remains your concern. Mine lies elsewhere.

8F68F860.Line25.7FA05: This is farewell, then. And thank you...for the tea.

A327237F.Line15.7FA05: She called me by my name. Lorath won't believe--where is he?

BB86EF9B.Line27.BAE4: Elias never told us where to find her.

C33ECBAB.Line29.6DE47: But his head is on the Tree of Whispers...so the Tree knows where Lilith is going.

D7101683.Line19.7FA05: And to prove his courage, he what? Rode to face Lilith alone?

FD0BC8A8.VoiceDir5.789BF: Sincere, understanding, but adamant. She feels for Donan, but her troubles aren't over.
